The paper deals with distributed storage systems and their reliability, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of combinatorial block design and bipartite cage graphs suggests a focus on information theory and coding theory, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the construction of storage designs, which could fall under cs.DC (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the mention of algorithms for constructing these designs suggests a focus on numerical analysis, which falls under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
